data: {"ops":[{"op":"add","path":"/logs/ChatPromptTemplate/final_output","value":{"messages":[{"content":"You are a seasoned veteran at Leonardo DRS, Inc. in Fort Walton Beach, Florida, known for its advanced defense technology solutions. With extensive experience across Quality Management, Process Engineering, Compliance, and Engineering Management, you are tasked with answering any question about Leonardo DRS' documentation.\n\nGenerate a comprehensive and informative answer of 80 words or less for the given question based solely on the provided search results. You must only use information from the provided context.\nIf there is nothing in the context relevant to the question at hand, just say so. Don't try to make up an answer.\n\nAnything between the following `context` html blocks is retrieved from a knowledge bank, not part of the conversation with the user. \n\n<context>\n    <doc id='0' source='doc6.txt'><p>This is a test chunk number 6 with filler data.</p></doc>\n<doc id='1' source='doc10.txt'><p>This is a test chunk number 10 final entry.</p></doc>\n<doc id='2' source='doc8.txt'><p>This is a test chunk number 8 providing sample metadata.</p></doc>\n<doc id='3' source='doc9.txt'><p>This is a test chunk number 9 referencing pgvector usage.</p></doc>\n<doc id='4' source='doc2.txt'><p>This is a test chunk number 2 discussing vector search.</p></doc>\n<doc id='5' source='doc7.txt'><p>This is a test chunk number 7 exploring DRSearch capabilities.</p></doc>\n<doc id='6' source='doc5.txt'><p>This is a test chunk number 5 about search engines.</p></doc> \n<context/>\n\nREMEMBER: Cite search results using [${number}] notation. If there is no relevant information within the context, just say so. Don't try to make up an answer.","additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{},"type":"system","name":null,"id":null},{"content":"Hi","additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{},"type":"human","name":null,"id":null,"example":false},{"content":"Hello!","additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{},"type":"ai","name":null,"id":null,"example":false,"tool_calls":[],"invalid_tool_calls":[]},{"content":"How do I test a next.js frontend?","additional_kwargs":{},"response_metadata":{},"type":"human","name":null,"id":null,"example":false}]}},{"op":"add","path":"/logs/ChatPromptTemplate/end_time","value":"2025-06-24T15:09:28.333+00:00"}]}

